{"name": "Chan Zuckerberg Initiative", "size": "\r\n                                    501-1k employees\r\n                                ", "status": "\r\n                                    Private\r\n                                ", "industry": "\r\n                            Data Processing, Education Services, Scientific Research\r\n                        ", "founded": "\r\n                                    2015\r\n                                ", "locations": ["801 Jefferson Ave, Redwood City, CA, 94063", "900 Middlefield Rd, Redwood City, CA, 94063", "601 Marshall Street, Redwood City, CA, 94063"], "company_technologies": ["amazon-web-services", "terraform", "kubernetes", "go", "wdl", "python", "ruby-on-rails", "sql", "reactjs", "prose-mirror", "snowflake-cloud-data-plat", "redis", "apache-kafka", "neo4j", "scipy", "tensorflow"], "about_company": ["\r\n                        ", "We are a new kind of philanthropy focused on engineering change at scale. Our engineering team partners with issue experts across our Science and Education Initiatives, to help bring technology to the table in new ways that drive solutions.\u00a0", "Our software engineers and machine learning experts bring the best software development innovations to the tools we build.\u00a0 We build for the long term whether your work is in engineering, product, design, or data & analytics, and we have a variety of different engineering teams:", "The Infrastructure Engineering team works across the organization to provide platforms, tools, and support for high leverage use cases. The team consists of three parts - core infrastructure, data infrastructure, and security infrastructure. The goal of the team is to reduce the infrastructure workload for our\u00a0 teams while making it easier for them to scale their infrastructure securely.\u00a0", "Some of our open source projects:", "Our team partners with educators at ", " to create learning experiences and tools - like those found in the Summit Learning Program - that meet the needs of every student and teacher. We partner with leading researchers in the fields of learning science and human development and teachers to build tools that help Summit Learning teachers at more than 380 schools differentiate instruction to meet the needs of every student.\u00a0 This includes dashboards that provide grade-level and subject matter reports on academic progress, as well a collaborative hub where teachers and specialists can connect on student support needs.\u00a0 Learn more about Summit Learning", ".\u00a0", "Meta is a web application built to help biomedical researchers stay up to date with the latest research as soon as it is available.\u00a0", "The Meta engineering teams use machine learning to map biomedical research in real-time. By analyzing and connecting millions of scientific outputs, including papers and preprints, Meta gives researchers the most comprehensive view of how science is evolving.", "The Single-Cell Engineering Team builds high-scale compute platforms and data visualization tools for the biomedical scientific community to accelerate ", ".We aim to help enable automated ", ".", "Current projects:", "The IDseq team is building a hypothesis-free global software system that helps scientists identify pathogens in metagenomic sequencing data.The platform works by rapidly combing through terabytes of metagenomic data for pathogens in a given sample \u2014 be they bacteria, viruses, fungi, or parasites. It has processed more than 50,000 samples to date and was even used to help identify and confirm the first case of COVID-19 in Cambodia at the onset of the global pandemic.We are working on extending IDseq's infrastructure, algorithms and visualizations to suit the pathogen characterization needs of partners around the world.", "Some of our open source repos:", "The Imaging Team builds software tools focused on enabling researchers to gain a much deeper mechanistic understanding of biological systems. Those software tools will help researchers to visualize life\u2019s processes at the necessary biological scales (systems, tissues, cells, proteins) and in the necessary context (e.g. protein interaction in cells, cell signaling in the living system), enable measurement and quantitative insights, and make and build on each other\u2019s discoveries.\u00a0\u00a0", "Our projects:", "Visit our ", "to read more about some of our projects, engineering tools, the people we build for, and what it\u2019s like to bring technical skills to solve some of the world\u2019s toughest challenges."], "people": ["https://stackoverflow.com/users/story/14121440", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/4760896/jessica-gadling?tab=profile", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/13939030/omar-valenzuela?tab=profile", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/story/12191920", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1380386/weaver?tab=profile", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/story/5317619"], "jobs_openings": ["543325", "560740", "560739", "560738", "560737", "560736", "560735", "537683", "537682", "537679"]}
