{"name": "Just Eat Takeaway.com", "size": "\r\n                                    10k+ employees\r\n                                ", "status": "\r\n                                    Public\r\n                                ", "industry": "\r\n                            Food & Beverage, Marketplace\r\n                        ", "founded": "\r\n                                    2000\r\n                                ", "locations": ["The Netherlands\nAmsterdam - Head Office\nOosterdoksstraat 80\n1011 DK Amsterdam", "Israel\nTel Aviv\n\u05de\u05d9\u05d3\u05d8\u05d0\u05d5\u05df, \u05e7\u05d5\u05de\u05d4 32\nDerech Menachem Begin 144\nTel Aviv-Yafo", "Germany\nBerlin\nCuvrystra\u00dfe 50-54. \n10997 Berlin", "Bulgaria\nSofia\nBulevard Bulgaria 109\n1404\nSofia\n (Vertigo Business Tower - floor -1 - office 27)", "The Netherlands\nEnschede\nBrouwerijstraat 10\n7523 XD Enschede", "United Kingdom\nFleet Place House\n2 Fleet Place\nLondon\nEC4M 7RF", "United Kingdom\nBroad Quay House (BQH)\nBroad Quay\nBristol \nBS1 4DJ", "Canada \nSuite 410-242 Hargrave Street\nWinnipeg\nMB, R3C 0M8", "Canada\n1010, 140-4th Street Avenue\nSW, Calgary\nAB, T2P 3N3"], "company_technologies": ["azure", "c#", ".net", "javascript", "react", "angular", "kubernetes", "kotlin", "swift", "java", "php", "mongodb", "sql", "docker", "servicebus"], "about_company": ["\r\n                        ", "We have hundreds of developers in multiple locations, working on dozens of exciting products and projects. Here's a brief rundown of some of the innovative work they\u2019re doing:", "The Takeaway Pay platform is built to offer companies the ability to treat their employees, with a budget for ordering with us.", "The big challenge was building a multi-national, multi-lingual, single-page application that\u2019s fully scalable and able to support millions of users. To do just that, we used the latest and greatest front-end tech stack like React, Redux, latest ECMAScript, NodeJS and more.", "As firm believers in continuous delivery methodologies such as automated testing, design systems and other best practices, we\u2019re able to deliver the best possible product for our users. Takeaway Pay\u2019s major backend components include APIs, background workers, databases, message brokers and a payment platform serving all employees\u2019 payments.\u00a0", "Meanwhile, the platform\u2019s backend components consist of microservices, serverless units, event-driven and async communication pipelines and infrastructure.", "Using .NET Core as the dominant framework, the Takeaway Pay platform is a genuine \u2018Born to the cloud\u2019 system. It\u2019s deployed to the Microsoft Azure cloud and combines tools like Function Apps, Service Bus, App Service, Redis Cache and others.", "----", "With hundreds of thousands of restaurant partners and hundreds of types of cuisine on our platform, we offer a wide range of delicious dishes to users. We\u2019re always looking for ways to make our product even better, helping customers to quickly and easily find their favourite food. Achieving this enables a great user experience and helps boost our restaurants\u2019 customer base.", "This is \u2018Food Discovery\u2019, and it\u2019s made possible by our talented teams. They focus on continually improving the personalisation of our apps, with recommendations for restaurants and dishes, as well as a personalised search ranking.", "By combining our data lake with an in-depth understanding of food, restaurants, customer preferences and delivery network performance, our data science teams deliver actionable insights through our Machine Learning platform, to support our product specialists.", "Using these insights, our engineers then implement compelling, personalised experiences for customers, restaurants and couriers across our platform. We\u2019re always looking for effective new tools to do this, but our current tech includes Google BigQuery, Airflow, Spark, Sagemaker, Snowplow, Tensorflow, ElasticSearch and Spark.", "----", "When one of our customers places an order, it sets many things in motion. Our delivery service gets into gear, the order is sent to the restaurant and the backend system is involved. This is where our arrival ratios, statistics and fallback systems come to life. \u2018Takeaway Transmissions\u2019 helps to connect all of these steps in an instant.", "The team behind Takeaway Transmissions has designed an infrastructure with methods like Event Storming and Domain-Driven Design. They link components together using Kafka or RabbitMQ, store data in NoSQL databases and run everything in Kubernetes.", "----", "The Job Dashboard application is a tool that lists all the jobs within a selected area or region. It also includes pages with job details and courier details.", "Our dashboard is reactive, working with React-Sagas and handling chunks of data by using a third-party package called react-window. Currently, we use two different API sources, one from the Integrations team and another from the Disposition team (which we\u2019re part of). We use Kubernetes to support deployment, and mostly work with Instana for logging.", "----", "Whether you\u2019re ordering from your favourite restaurant or trying to find that brilliant curry restaurant your friend mentioned, you\u2019re unknowingly using a complex service mesh. From the promoted restaurant you see appearing at the top of the list on our app to the restaurant portal used by our partners, it\u2019s all powered by services our Sofia team has built.", "We keep an open mind with infrastructure, choosing the best technology for each specific case. This enables us to deliver microservices in PHP and Java, or to build hyper-complex Laravel-powered stateless APIs and operate with events in Kafka and Rabbit MQ. It even lets us deliver cutting-edge frontend applications powered by Vue.Js, Typescript and Node.", "Our recipe is to pick the best language, work exclusively within containerised environments using Docker, implement the best security practices and deploy solutions with the help of tailored CI/CD stages. Then we add a comprehensive Unit/Feature testing suite, an in-depth Integration and Stress/Load tests conducted by our QAs.", "We combine this with a focus on maintainability and interoperability, following global coding standards and code-based consistency guidelines. The result is multiple mission-critical services deployed with zero downtime, handling millions of entities with a sub 90-minute latency.", "----", "Our Canadian teams run a full platform for their local SkipTheDishes brand including the customer website and application, partner-restaurant app and portal, as well as the courier app and ATS, scheduling dispatch and operation tools. Alongside this, they also handle our delco delivery platform infrastructure and take care of the courier networks for five other markets."], "people": ["https://stackoverflow.com/users/358679/wrikken?tab=profile", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/story/21574", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3856/gaz?tab=profile", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/story/963542", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3212/markedup?tab=profile", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/story/825114", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2560062/yenerunver?tab=profile", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/7146442/o-nassie?tab=profile", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/15409138/georgi-atanasov?tab=profile", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/15330282/gaetan-licci?tab=profile", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/15409136/maxim-sarandev?tab=profile", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/15131124/ezequiel-lauria?tab=profile", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/15328521/erich-radstake?tab=profile", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/15409150/lena-gainulina?tab=profile", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/15136306/oleg-cherevko?tab=profile", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/story/7064222", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/15329655/wesley-francisco?tab=profile", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/15409177/john-schreiber?tab=profile", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2092969/vinicius-cainelli?tab=profile", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5641284/oleg-tsibulevskiy?tab=profile", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/15382656/marcel-van-den-berg?tab=profile", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/15409226/nana-gavrielova?tab=profile", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2225808/stuart?tab=profile", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/15329604/a-m?tab=profile", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/15409247/sergei-gavrilov?tab=profile", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/15409385/jiyoung-hwang?tab=profile", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/15329851/kai?tab=profile", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/15137375/emre-akman?tab=profile", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/15183239/andrii-kuzminskyi?tab=profile", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/15147514/jeannie-flynn?tab=profile", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/15329523/lukasdeboer?tab=profile", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/15413299/guilherme-da-silva?tab=profile", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/story/2760832", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/13573619/tzvia-keren?tab=profile", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/15131141/roel?tab=profile", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/6725671/acemoo?tab=profile", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/15092720/eugi?tab=profile", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/story/5952758", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/story/1677079", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/15414193/nathan-may?tab=profile", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/15131120/maxim-vetrenko?tab=profile", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/15414398/anfan-li?tab=profile", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/9676318/sam?tab=profile", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/story/7514874", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/15130105/jack-cordner?tab=profile", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/15432027/phoebe-hadley?tab=profile", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/12032860/andre-didier?tab=profile", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1887802/st