{"name": "Western Governors University", "size": "\r\n                                    5k-10k employees\r\n                                ", "status": "\r\n                                    Private\r\n                                ", "industry": "\r\n                            Higher Education, Non-Profit\r\n                        ", "founded": "\r\n                                    1997\r\n                                ", "locations": ["Salt Lake City, UT", "Austin, TX", "Phoenix, AZ"], "company_technologies": ["java", "angular", "oracle", "postgresql", "amazon-web-services", "aws-fargate", "aws-codepipeline", "apache-kafka", "amazon-rds-aurora", "amazon-dynamodb", "python", "newrelic", "kotlin", "swift"], "about_company": ["\r\n                        ", "Our infrastructure is built on Amazon Web Services, with an emphasis on containerized applications running in ECS Fargate. Applications are typically built in Java, with teams starting to branch out in Python and Kotlin. All Production code is built and deployed using CI/CD best practices in AWS CodePipeline, to ensure minimal downtime and quality control on software being deployed. We are always looking for areas to investigate new technology and\u00a0understanding how we\u00a0can improve our services' stability and performance.", "The Platform Services team at WGU designs and builds shared infrastructure and services inside the AWS cloud environment. This shared infrastructure is used by our software engineering teams to deploy applications utilized by WGU students and faculty. Platform Services is focused on developing automated tools that will build, scan, test, and deploy applications. This automated approach allows developers at WGU to focus on their code and what they do best.", "Platform Services focuses on utilizing services in AWS that facilitate automating the process outlined above such as, CloudFormation, CodePipeline, and CodeBuild providing software engineering teams a CI/CD process to deploying their applications. Platform Services has developed over 10 pipelines allowing teams to deploy AWS services such as; Lambda, DynamoDB, ECS, SQS, and S3. Platform Services utilize languages such as Bash/Shell scripts, Python3, and Java to aid us in building out and testing these automated solutions.", "The WGU Beyond team has a generalist focus, facilitating innovation and bringing new technologies, vendors, partnerships, stacks, and solutions into the organization. With an eye on rapid proof-of-concept projects, a team member will have the opportunity and expectation to pick up a technology, rapidly gain understanding and proficiency and then implement a showcase project. They will also have the chance to demonstrate this technology to leaders as well as the organization as a whole. These projects might be oriented on simulated student experiences, secops, devops, artificial intelligence, analytics, automation, feature expansion, industry trends or just outright exploration. Ideas are rapidly triaged and executed in an effort to make sure the organization as a whole has visibility on emerging tech and trends in order to further WGU\u2019s mission.", "Languages, frameworks, platforms, and technologies are not fixed, rather using each proof-of-concept as a chance to flex engineering muscles and vet out new possibilities. Write a Python-based computer vision app one day, a Kotlin microservice the next, and test out infrastructural experiments in between. Perhaps a student experience will be honed in Vue, React, Angular, or another emerging framework. The key is a rapid adjustment, a tinkerer\u2019s spirit, and a drive to see it manifested as fast as possible!"], "people": null, "jobs_openings": ["558415", "558411", "558054", "539791", "551762", "550609"]}
