{"name": "Viva Wallet", "size": "\r\n                                    501-1k employees\r\n                                ", "status": "\r\n                                    Private\r\n                                ", "industry": "\r\n                            Financial Services\r\n                        ", "founded": "\r\n                                    2010\r\n                                ", "locations": ["18-20 Amarousiou-Chalandriou Avenue, Marousi (Arcania business center)"], "company_technologies": [".net", "vuejs", "reactjs", "sqlserver", "azurecosmosdb", "azuretablestorage", "redis", "c#", "asp.net", "androidstudio", "kotlin", "java", "xcode", "swift", "c++", "mvvm", "mvp", "gitflow", "selenium", "appium", "rest-assured"], "about_company": ["\r\n                        ", "As we are building the payments of the future, we aim to create a truly unified seamless payments system for Europe and the UK. Over the years, our technological stack grew larger and our expertise more solid, allowing us to build Viva Wallet 100% based on Microsoft Azure.", "Core services are written in C#, ASP.NET and .NET Core is the choice for everything new. The latest Front-End applications have been developed using VueJS and ReactJS, whilst older apps use technologies such as Razor and jQuery.", "Our backends leverage Microsoft SQL Server, Azure Cosmos DB and Azure Table Storage. In some cases, we boost the performance with tools like Redis.", "Our mobile apps and SDKs are developed with native tools, using Android Studio with Kotlin and Java and Xcode with Swift. We use C/C++ when low-level coding is required, either interacting with external hardware modules or when maximum security is crucial. We implement architectures such as MVVM / MVP and are always keen to explore new ones.", "The Viva Wallet POS payment app, interacts with peripherals such as card terminal readers and printers over Bluetooth or USB and the mobile device NFC module.", "Cryptography is at the core of every application we design. We make payment services and data processing secure, by implementing strong industry standards in symmetric & asymmetric cryptographic techniques, key exchange protocols, and tokenisation. Our code interfaces with cryptographic security modules, hardware, and cloud-based, to protect keys and secrets.", "Where Viva's culture among developers shines, is when front-end and back-end development teams are brought together to design and create heavy-armored end-user applications with niche protection technologies, such as white box cryptography, obfuscation, sandboxing, and end-to-end encryption.", "We use Github for our code and follow the Gitflow branching model for our development. We organise our work boards with Jira and Confluence, and we have adopted the CI/CD approach, to automate all our builds and releases.", "During the development process, our QA team performs thorough testing. Selenium with Selenoid is used for UI testing, Appium for Mobile test automation, and Rest-assured for API, all using Java as the core of the frameworks."], "people": ["https://stackoverflow.com/users/15335622/makis-antypas?tab=profile", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2432245/anthony-t?tab=profile", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/15335862/yannis-michalis?tab=profile", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2166197/george-gkionis?tab=profile", "https://stackoverflow.com/users/15337145/george-liaskos?tab=profile"], "jobs_openings": ["541474", "523118", "540007"]}
