{"name": "Shape A/S", "size": "\r\n                                    51-200 employees\r\n                                ", "status": "\r\n                                    Private\r\n                                ", "industry": "\r\n                            Mobile Application, Product Development, Software Development\r\n                        ", "founded": "\r\n                                    2010\r\n                                ", "locations": ["Njalsgade 17A, Pakhus 2, 2. sal\nDK-2300 Copenhagen"], "company_technologies": ["ios", "android", "kotlin", "swift", "ruby", "amazon-web-services", "reactive-programming"], "about_company": ["\r\n                        ", "We strongly believe that the best possible mobile applications are made using native technologies, so for Android and iOS we always use Kotlin and Swift. We care about making code that is solid, reliable and maintainable.", "Our backend team enable our apps to perform with speed at scale and are typically build with Kotlin and hosted on AWS. It is our philosophy that\u00a0infrastructure should also be defined as code and the same people who write the application logic also write the cloud infrastructure.", "The backend systems we develop and run are the brains of our apps. We design services in a way so they can reliably, and with great performance, power our apps. It is important for us to build systems using architectural patterns that allow us to scale up with increased demand, but also allow us to easily make changes when new business requirements surface", "Through code reviews we help each other ensure a high code quality, but we also use it as a tool to learn from each other and improve ourselves.", "We deploy our services to AWS using CloudFormation and CDK. Having all infrastructure as code ensures that we can easily spin up new environments and reuse infrastructure definitions between multiple services.", "With more than 30 full time iOS developers working at Shape we are probably the one place in Denmark with most knowledge and enthusiasm for developing great apps for Apple platforms. We have developed many libraries that we share between multiple projects in order drive a modular approach.", "Each team has full autonomy to choose the best tools and design patterns for the task at hand so you will experience different approaches in different teams. For example the Shape Games iOS team makes heavy use of Functional Reactive Programming using our own library ReactiveKit (API compatible with Apple\u2019s Combine framework) whereas other teams prefer other approaches. Combined with our knowledge-sharing culture this helps to drive innovation across all development teams.", "We are more than 30 talented android developers in Shape so it is guaranteed that you will be challenged and that you will have very experienced colleagues to learn from and share your knowledge with. The different development teams are empowered to choose the tools they prefer, but some of the technologies we really like are Kotlin coroutines and Kotlin Flow. Speaking of Kotlin, we were one of the first adopters and we have not looked back at Java ever since. When developing Android apps we use a number of internal libraries as well as well-know open source ones."], "people": null, "jobs_openings": ["369999", "557005", "370009"]}
