{"name": "Octopus Deploy", "size": "\r\n                                    51-200 employees\r\n                                ", "status": "\r\n                                    Private\r\n                                ", "industry": "\r\n                            Continuous Delivery, DevOps, Software Development\r\n                        ", "founded": "\r\n                                    2012\r\n                                ", "locations": ["Suite 4, 540 Queen Street, Brisbane"], "company_technologies": [".net", "c#", "sql-server", "octopus-deploy", "teamcity", "github", "azure", "amazon-web-services", "powershell", ".net-core", "asp.net-core"], "about_company": ["\r\n                        ", "Octopus is built with C# and .NET Core 5. There's a central Octopus server that runs as a service, exposing REST services using ASP.NET. It\u00a0communicates with remote agents (Tentacles) to execute deployments. The UI is a React SPA.\u00a0", "One of the most enjoyable aspects of working on Octopus is the variety of technical challenges:", "One day you might be rewriting part of the UI in React to speed it up, the next you might be investigating why a clustered Octopus Server is performing slowing during a 3000-machine deployment.\u00a0", "We keep our code in GitHub, and we try to open source as much as we can. We spend most of the day in Slack, and meet online with Zoom.\u00a0"], "people": null, "jobs_openings": ["554199", "541375", "541378", "529032", "541377"]}
