{"name": "Percona Staffing LLC", "size": "\r\n                                    201-500 employees\r\n                                ", "status": "\r\n                                    Private\r\n                                ", "industry": "\r\n                            Databases, DBaaS, Software Development / Engineering\r\n                        ", "founded": "\r\n                                    2006\r\n                                ", "locations": ["Percona\nPO Box 1126\nDurham, NC 27702-1126, USA"], "company_technologies": ["c", "c++", "python", "kubernetes", "shell", "javascript", "grafana", "jenkins", "mysql", "postgresql", "mongodb", "go", "amazon-ec2", "google-cloud-platform", "linux", "open-source", "markdown"], "about_company": ["\r\n                        ", "Percona is a pure open source company. There is no fee or commercial license requirement for downloading and using our software.", "All of our software we create and maintain is released under Open Source licenses. Many of these components are part of our server distributions for MongoDB, MySQL and PostgreSQL, but there are standalone projects and tools as well. Some examples include Percona Xtrabackup, Percona Backup for MongoDB or Percona Monitoring and Management. These projects are developed in a wide range of languages like C/C++, Go or Python (and others). We make all of these available on github and we encourage collaboration and contributions around these projects.", "We also take upstream Open Source projects and enhance these by applying modifications and improvements. In this model, the majority of the development work is done by the respective upstream communities, and Percona is participating in these by submitting bug reports or patches (the level of engagement varies by project). Some examples in this category include Percona Server for MySQL or Percona XtraDB Cluster, a high-availability solution.", "To achieve these goals, we make use of countless Open Source project